Package it.polimi.ingsw.server.controller.powerup

Class Powerup

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.ingsw.server.controller.powerup.Powerup
  • public class Powerup
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a controller-side Powerup and it's used to generalize all the effects

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class Description
      static class  Powerup.Target
      Enum containing the different target types that the controller should use to determine which players can be affected by this powerup
      static class  Powerup.TargetConstraint
      Enum containing the different constraints a target must satisfy to be affected by the powerup effect
      static class  Powerup.Trigger
      Enum containing the different name of triggers that the controller should use to determine when to ask the player if he wants to activate his powerup

    • Constructor Detail

      • Powerup

        public Powerup​(java.lang.String name,
               Powerup.Trigger trigger,
               Powerup.Target target,
               Powerup.TargetConstraint targetConstraint,
               int cost,
               TriConsumer<Player,​Player,​Interviewer> effect)
        Constructs a controller-side powerup configured with the desired effect
        Parameters:
        name - the powerup name associated with this powerup
        trigger - the kind of trigger that makes this powerup available for the player
        target - the kind of target this powerup effect can affect
        targetConstraint - the kind of constraint a target must satisfy
        cost - the cost of the effect that the powerup owner should pay before the activation
        effect - the consumer that will manage the powerup effect
